title: 60 Minutes AU - 17-7-2016
description:
60 Minutes AU - 17-7-2016

Australian tourists Angie Jackson and Tommy Williams found themselves prey Samoa's most dangerous criminal. Michael Usher travelled to some of America's most racially segregated communities and discovered a simmering underbelly of anger and resentment that's very close to erupting into open war. Jennifer Saunders and Joanna Lumley are back playing the somewhat hopeless, often sozzled, but always funny Edina and Patsy, in the Ab Fab feature film
